Parliament, Monday, 27 August 2018 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow be briefed by State Information Technology Agency (Sita) on forensic report on the contracts involving Rofin and Fundudzi. Details of the briefing:
	Date: Tuesday, 28 August 2018
	Time: 09:30
	Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building After the briefing tomorrow, Scopa will hold a hearing with Eskom to review Eskom’s deviations and expansions. Details of the hearing:
	Date: Tuesday, 28 August 2018
	Time: 18:00
	Venue: Committee Room E249, Second Floor, National Assembly Building. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI. For media enquiries, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
